Where you going to hide the cash?

235
00:11:29.080 --> 00:11:31.760
You don't ever want to get caught slipping
with both of them in the same place.

236
00:11:32.960 --> 00:11:34.160
What classes you taking in school?

237
00:11:35.280 --> 00:11:40.480
Biology. philosophy. economics.
pre-calc. Italian. and history.

238
00:11:40.600 --> 00:11:41.640
That's what I thought.

239
00:11:41.800 --> 00:11:43.240
they ain't teaching you the shit
that I'm doing.

240
00:11:44.440 --> 00:11:47.000
Let's hold on your supply.
You got more to learn.

241
00:11:47.920 --> 00:11:50.920
I got to recruit a few niggas.
I think you learn a thing or two.

242
00:11:52.160 --> 00:11:53.080
You coming or not?

243
00:11:53.960 --> 00:11:54.920
Yeah.

244
00:12:00.120 --> 00:12:02.840
Quinn. This is Diego Martinez.

245
00:12:02.960 --> 00:12:05.400
He will be overseeing
my clubs while I'm out of town.

246
00:12:05.560 --> 00:12:07.000
so. I just wanted you two
to get to know each other.

247
00:12:08.120 --> 00:12:09.240
Well. it's a good thing you hired him.

248
00:12:09.360 --> 00:12:11.520
because you are going to Paris
sooner than expected.

249
00:12:12.000 --> 00:12:12.960
I like the sound of that.

250
00:12:13.760 --> 00:12:16.800
Diego. do you feel comfortable
taking over operations so quickly?

251
00:12:17.120 --> 00:12:19.480
Yeah. yeah. Mr. Coleman and I
have known each other

252
00:12:19.680 --> 00:12:20.600
for a long time.

253
00:12:20.720 --> 00:12:22.400
I'm familiar with the way
he likes to run things.

254
00:12:22.560 --> 00:12:24.800
And you have a background in nightclubs
and entertainment?

255
00:12:25.800 --> 00:12:28.520
I grew up helping my cousins
run restaurants in Miami.

256
00:12:28.920 --> 00:12:30.400
Shit. when I was 18. I started promoting.

257
00:12:31.040 --> 00:12:32.440
Been in nightclubs ever since.

258
00:12:33.080 --> 00:12:35.000
Well. it seems like we are in good hands.

259
00:12:36.280 --> 00:12:37.360
So. you can call me anytime.

260
00:12:38.120 --> 00:12:40.280
Andre. my office will be in touch
about travel plans.

261
00:12:44.520 --> 00:12:45.640
Okay...

262
00:12:46.880 --> 00:12:50.120
That was. uh. a good touch
on that Miami story. man. That was nice.

263
00:12:51.160 --> 00:12:52.560
Why's that got to be a story?

264
00:12:53.760 --> 00:12:54.880
Yeah. bring it in.

265
00:12:57.840 --> 00:12:59.600
It's good to see you again. Kanan.

266
00:13:02.120 --> 00:13:03.160
What's with the kid?

267
00:13:04.480 --> 00:13:06.600
You got all your bodyguards.
I thought I should bring mine.

268
00:13:07.520 --> 00:13:08.520
[chuckles]

269
00:13:09.440 --> 00:13:10.600
What can I do for you?

270
00:13:11.640 --> 00:13:14.120
I know you've been down a supplier
since that shootout shit.

271
00:13:14.320 --> 00:13:15.640
I want to be your next one.

272
00:13:17.480 --> 00:13:20.760
I thought you worked for Tommy.
He send you here?

273
00:13:20.880 --> 00:13:22.400
Tommy's out the game for a minute.

274
00:13:22.880 --> 00:13:24.640
He had some issues with a former partner

275
00:13:24.840 --> 00:13:26.800
who was like a brother to him.
Real sad shit.

276
00:13:27.440 --> 00:13:29.960
Turns out. his boy. Ghost.
is who called the hit

277
00:13:30.120 --> 00:13:32.120
that got your boy. Nicolas.
here popped in the leg.

278
00:13:33.880 --> 00:13:35.240
Well. you're going
to take care of him. right?

279
00:13:37.800 --> 00:13:39.080
Sorry to hear of these troubles.

280
00:13:39.520 --> 00:13:42.840
I'm running my own game now.
Same product. better price.

281
00:13:43.080 --> 00:13:44.200
Just none of Tommy's drama.

282
00:13:44.840 --> 00:13:46.360
That shit Tommy got you was good. right?

283
00:13:47.720 --> 00:13:50.240
It's selling well. no complaints.

284
00:13:50.560 --> 00:13:51.480
So what we waiting for?

285
00:13:53.360 --> 00:13:56.800
-[in Italian] Think we can trust this guy?
-Yes.

286
00:13:56.920 --> 00:13:58.240
You can trust him.

287
00:13:58.440 --> 00:13:59.400
[in English] What's that. 'Riq?

288
00:14:00.360 --> 00:14:02.560
I asked if I could trust you.
He says I can.

289
00:14:04.880 --> 00:14:06.480
Now I see why you brought the kid.

290
00:14:07.840 --> 00:14:09.680
We're going to do this on a trial basis.

291
00:14:11.360 --> 00:14:13.280
[phone clicks. taps]

292
00:14:15.520 --> 00:14:16.680
What are we getting
from just sitting here?

293
00:14:16.800 --> 00:14:17.960
Shh.

294
00:14:18.720 --> 00:14:20.640
[indistinct chatter]

295
00:14:26.000 --> 00:14:27.160
They look like us.

296
00:14:28.080 --> 00:14:30.240
Except Dre got Crustyballs in a suit.

297
00:14:31.080 --> 00:14:33.280
Punk-ass pretty boy bitch motherfucker.

298
00:14:33.720 --> 00:14:35.520
Why would he be bringing
Cristobal into the clubs?

299
00:14:35.760 --> 00:14:36.800
Why would he do that?

300
00:14:38.000 --> 00:14:38.960
Who the fuck cares?

301
00:14:39.960 --> 00:14:42.040
Now we know where Dre's spot is.
we'll catch him here.

302
00:14:42.640 --> 00:14:44.640
Now. I got a little family dinner
I got to get to.

303
00:14:46.040 --> 00:14:47.640
You couldn't invite a brother? Damn. man.

304
00:14:48.480 --> 00:14:50.200
Oh. okay. I get it.
your other family. okay.

305
00:14:50.520 --> 00:14:52.240
So. you still drinking
Teresi's Kool-Aid. cool.

306
00:14:52.360 --> 00:14:54.920
Look. since you got plans in your head.
but you don't like to share.

307
00:14:55.040 --> 00:14:56.800
you let me know when you ready
to make a move.

308
00:14:57.280 --> 00:14:58.600
I'ma walk from here.

309
00:15:02.560 --> 00:15:04.280
[elevator bell dings]

310
00:15:08.040 --> 00:15:09.680
What. is she here to arrest you
or something?

311
00:15:10.200 --> 00:15:11.280
She's here to help.

312
00:15:11.920 --> 00:15:13.440
Help who? Dad?

313
00:15:14.120 --> 00:15:15.080
No.

314
00:15:15.520 --> 00:15:18.520
Your dad is not involved in this.
He knows nothing about it.

315
00:15:19.400 --> 00:15:22.560
-It's just us.
-[Angela] I'm here to help your mom.

316
00:15:23.200 --> 00:15:24.560
And to help you.

317
00:15:27.040 --> 00:15:29.280
-I don't trust her.
-[Tasha] But I do.

318
00:15:30.960 --> 00:15:33.000
When it comes to this. Come here.

319
00:15:35.640 --> 00:15:37.600
[Angela] I need information
about Raymond Jones.

320
00:15:37.920 --> 00:15:39.160
About who he was working with.

321
00:15:40.120 --> 00:15:41.760
Anything you have will be helpful.

322
00:15:43.960 --> 00:15:46.840
All right. well. he used to hang out
with this woman named Jukebox.

323
00:15:46.960 --> 00:15:48.280
She was a dirty cop from D.C.

324
00:15:48.880 --> 00:15:49.960
They ran licks together.

325
00:15:50.200 --> 00:15:52.440
They used their uniforms as a disguise.
I guess.

326
00:15:53.880 --> 00:15:55.320
How did you meet Jukebox?

327
00:15:55.880 --> 00:15:57.440
Through a friend. Kanan.

328
00:15:58.120 --> 00:15:59.640
[Angela] Does Kanan know Raymond Jones?

329
00:16:00.200 --> 00:16:02.760
[Tariq] Yeah. he knew him.
but they never kicked it.

330
00:16:03.560 --> 00:16:04.680
Where's Jukebox now?

331
00:16:06.320 --> 00:16:10.680
I believe she's dead.
Kanan killed her. right?

332
00:16:10.960 --> 00:16:12.440
This is what you wanted me
to come home for?

333
00:16:12.560 --> 00:16:17.960
Your mother tells me your friend. Kanan.
may have killed his son. Shawn Stark.

334
00:16:19.080 --> 00:16:20.560
Do you know anything about that?

335
00:16:24.440 --> 00:16:27.080
You're framing Kanan like you
and Ghost did when I was a little kid.

336
00:16:28.920 --> 00:16:33.000
-Yes. he needs to take the rap.
-You're working with her.

337
00:16:34.200 --> 00:16:35.720
The woman that ruined our lives.

338
00:16:36.320 --> 00:16:38.160
The woman that broke
our whole family apart.

339
00:16:38.480 --> 00:16:41.160
The woman who arrested Ghost
for the one thing he didn't fucking do.

340
00:16:43.320 --> 00:16:44.400
I knew Ghost was a traitor.

341
00:16:45.040 --> 00:16:47.000
I thought maybe he made you
help him set up Kanan.

342
00:16:47.720 --> 00:16:48.800
But you're no better.

343
00:16:49.200 --> 00:16:52.040
-You're a fucking backstabber. too.
-You better listen to me. boy.

344
00:16:52.640 --> 00:16:55.360
Catching the charge for Ray Ray
is the least Kanan deserves.

345
00:16:55.720 --> 00:16:59.000
No matter what me and your dad have done.
Kanan has done worse.

346
00:16:59.720 --> 00:17:02.960
He killed Shawn. his own son.
Don't you forget that.

347
00:17:03.720 --> 00:17:04.720
He was good to me.

348
00:17:05.000 --> 00:17:07.000
Ain't nobody in the goddamn
history of the world

349
00:17:07.240 --> 00:17:08.480
been better to you than me.

350
00:17:08.920 --> 00:17:10.000
I'm your mother!

351
00:17:11.480 --> 00:17:12.960
I could go to jail for this.

352
00:17:14.800 --> 00:17:15.800
Tariq...

353
00:17:16.520 --> 00:17:17.440
it's either me...

354
00:17:19.320 --> 00:17:20.280
or Kanan.

355
00:17:25.000 --> 00:17:26.360
Find another way. Ma.

356
00:17:28.960 --> 00:17:30.120
'Riq!

357
00:17:32.160 --> 00:17:33.600
[sobs]

358
00:17:34.320 --> 00:17:35.960
[vocalizing]

359
00:17:36.080 --> 00:17:37.320
-[Tommy] Hey.
-Hello!

360
00:17:37.440 --> 00:17:38.920
-You made it.
-Look at you!

361
00:17:39.960 --> 00:17:40.960
-Come on.
-Oh. wow.

362
00:17:41.080 --> 00:17:42.440
-Right?
-Wow. wow. wow.

363
00:17:42.600 --> 00:17:44.360
Welcome to my humble abode.

364
00:17:44.560 --> 00:17:46.920
I told you. Hey. Tommy. Tommy.

365
00:17:47.640 --> 00:17:49.720
-I got you this.
-It smells so good in here.

366
00:17:49.840 --> 00:17:51.200
-It's wine.
-Doesn't it smell good?

367
00:17:51.440 --> 00:17:53.600
-Mm-hmm.
-[Tommy] Oh. Chianti.

368
00:17:54.680 --> 00:17:56.000
-[chuckles]
-Do you have a cook?

369
00:17:56.400 --> 00:17:58.520
Hi. welcome.

370
00:17:58.960 --> 00:18:01.280
Hey. this is Connie. and my dad.

371
00:18:01.640 --> 00:18:04.360
-This is my girl. LaKeisha.
-It's nice to meet you both.

372
00:18:04.480 --> 00:18:05.960
-[laughs] Hi!
-Nice to meet you.

373
00:18:06.240 --> 00:18:07.880
-It's nice to meet you.
-It's nice to meet you.

374
00:18:08.000 --> 00:18:09.120
How you doing?

375
00:18:09.960 --> 00:18:11.280
Oh. goodness. you're beautiful.

376
00:18:11.480 --> 00:18:14.080
Thank you. You could use
some of your dad's charm.

377
00:18:14.240 --> 00:18:16.120
Oh. you ain't even heard him
speak Italian yet.

378
00:18:16.320 --> 00:18:18.320
How did that go. Dad?
[speaks broken Italian]

379
00:18:18.480 --> 00:18:20.760
-Come on.
-[speaks Italian]

380
00:18:21.240 --> 00:18:24.080
Oh. I don't know what half
of what I just ate was.

381
00:18:24.320 --> 00:18:25.520
but it was delicious.

382
00:18:26.000 --> 00:18:27.200
My compliments to the chef.

383
00:18:27.560 --> 00:18:28.920
-Thank you.
-Wow.

384
00:18:29.320 --> 00:18:31.400
Yo. Connie. I got to tell you.
you one smart woman.

385
00:18:32.200 --> 00:18:34.160
Me and the old man. we checked
out an ambulance place.

386
00:18:34.400 --> 00:18:37.040
-It was perfect.
-Mm. good. good.

387
00:18:37.400 --> 00:18:40.760
I'm happy to have helped you
in your. um. search.

388
00:18:42.120 --> 00:18:43.800
Oh. no. no. no. no. It's all good.

389
00:18:45.080 --> 00:18:46.480
I don't keep nothing from 'Keisha.

390
00:18:47.040 --> 00:18:49.400
Really? You trust her that much?

391
00:18:50.960 --> 00:18:51.960
I do.

392
00:18:52.560 --> 00:18:54.000
[Connie] That's easy to say now.

393
00:18:54.400 --> 00:18:57.840
But wait until they've locked her
in a box for two days.

394
00:18:59.200 --> 00:19:00.960
See if you feel the same way then.

395
00:19:02.040 --> 00:19:03.560
Well. it wouldn't be the first time.

396
00:19:04.040 --> 00:19:06.120
Yeah. we've been through
some shit together already.

397
00:19:06.800 --> 00:19:08.040
'Keisha ride or die.

398
00:19:08.160 --> 00:19:09.480
I don't know what the fuck you're saying.

399
00:19:09.600 --> 00:19:12.000
-[all laugh]
-I don't mean to be rude.

400
00:19:12.720 --> 00:19:16.680
but men like these.
it's more hard than easy.

401
00:19:17.240 --> 00:19:19.520
They took Tony away for 25 years.

402
00:19:20.280 --> 00:19:21.800
I thought he'd never come back.

403
00:19:23.080 --> 00:19:26.560
Right now. we're lucky.
We're living on borrowed time.

404
00:19:27.640 --> 00:19:28.760
You know what?

405
00:19:30.320 --> 00:19:32.960
-You never let me down.
-No.

406
00:19:33.880 --> 00:19:36.680
Because I love you.

407
00:19:37.600 --> 00:19:39.120
You dumb palooka.

408
00:19:42.480 --> 00:19:44.240
[LaKeisha] Well. we've been through
some shit. too.

409
00:19:44.800 --> 00:19:46.960
I thought we was through.
but then Tommy came back

410
00:19:47.080 --> 00:19:50.600
into my life. and I really feel like
he has my back this time.

411
00:19:51.840 --> 00:19:52.760
Yeah.

412
00:19:53.560 --> 00:19:55.080
I'm in for whatever.

413
00:19:55.960 --> 00:19:57.960
That's hard to find in a man.
so. when you find it.

414
00:19:58.560 --> 00:19:59.560
you don't let it go.

415
00:20:00.320 --> 00:20:03.200
Well. in that case.
welcome to the family. 'Keisha.

416
00:20:03.440 --> 00:20:04.400
[laughs]

417
00:20:04.520 --> 00:20:05.960
<i>-Salud.
-</i>[LaKeisha]<i> Salud.</i>

418
00:20:06.080 --> 00:20:07.160
<i>Salud.</i>

419
00:20:09.480 --> 00:20:11.160
Andre Coleman.

420
00:20:12.560 --> 00:20:14.680
And LaVerne Ganner. Kanan's cousin.

421
00:20:14.840 --> 00:20:15.880
[knock on door]

422
00:20:20.440 --> 00:20:21.400
Thought you took the day off.

423
00:20:23.080 --> 00:20:24.040
I didn't.

424
00:20:25.360 --> 00:20:28.600
So how's my recommendation
coming along. Boss?

425
00:20:29.160 --> 00:20:33.960
How's your independent investigation
into Tommy Egan coming along. John?

426
00:20:35.080 --> 00:20:36.840
-So. you know.
-[Angela] I know.

427
00:20:38.000 --> 00:20:40.520
And I want to know
what you're keeping from me.

428
00:20:41.600 --> 00:20:43.200
Don't we all want
to get the bad guys here?

429
00:20:44.040 --> 00:20:44.960
Cute.

430
00:20:47.080 --> 00:20:49.440
-And way to play the white hat.
-[chuckles]

431
00:20:50.480 --> 00:20:51.840
This is Saxe. huh?

432
00:20:53.520 --> 00:20:58.120
Don't get caught up in his vendetta. John.
It predates you. it predates Greg.

433
00:20:58.680 --> 00:21:01.720
Saxe has always been out to get me
and never won.

434
00:21:03.240 --> 00:21:05.240
You're really going to give up
a corner office

435
00:21:05.440 --> 00:21:08.080
with an entire team
who answers to you in D.C.

436
00:21:08.360 --> 00:21:09.360
for Cooper Saxe?

437
00:21:12.200 --> 00:21:15.120
I can't wait to get as far away
from this office as possible.

438
00:21:16.520 --> 00:21:20.520
We got a CI. some old guy close to Tommy.
but nothing concrete yet.

439
00:21:22.400 --> 00:21:24.920
-What's his name?
-Confidential informant.

440
00:21:26.520 --> 00:21:28.880
It's Saxe's contact. and he's playing
it close to the vest.

441
00:21:33.520 --> 00:21:34.920
So are you gonna call D.C. or what?

442
00:21:42.400 --> 00:21:44.040
[keypad beeps]

443
00:21:45.160 --> 00:21:46.400
We got good news. Tash.

444
00:21:47.240 --> 00:21:49.840
Angela got us surveillance of Dre
and Ray Ray in the street together.

445
00:21:49.960 --> 00:21:51.280
which means they're officially linked.

446
00:21:53.320 --> 00:21:54.280
Great.

447
00:21:55.200 --> 00:21:57.120
So. I just got to get her
a few more details

448
00:21:57.320 --> 00:22:01.200
so. she can make her full case.
and me and Tommy take care of Dre.

449
00:22:01.320 --> 00:22:03.000
[inhales]

450
00:22:03.120 --> 00:22:05.200
Would it be better
to maybe frame somebody

451
00:22:05.320 --> 00:22:06.680
with a lower profile?

452
00:22:07.000 --> 00:22:08.520
Dre's profile ain't as high as he acts.

453
00:22:10.120 --> 00:22:11.840
I mean. somebody who's completely
off the radar.

454
00:22:12.160 --> 00:22:14.400
No family. no friends. no job.

455
00:22:15.200 --> 00:22:16.680
Somebody nobody would miss.

456
00:22:17.440 --> 00:22:20.240
Sure. but I don't know anybody else
in Ray Ray's crew.

457
00:22:22.640 --> 00:22:23.880
What about Kanan?

458
00:22:28.560 --> 00:22:31.440
-[scoffs]
-Kanan saved our son.

459
00:22:31.960 --> 00:22:33.440
Dre put him in harm's way.

460
00:22:33.560 --> 00:22:35.520
See. you don't want to target Kanan.

461
00:22:35.640 --> 00:22:37.120
because it would mean
you would have to admit

462
00:22:37.240 --> 00:22:39.240
that everything that's happened
is your fault.

463
00:22:39.960 --> 00:22:42.160
The shooting at Truth. Killing Rolla.

464
00:22:42.440 --> 00:22:45.000
Everything about Tariq. Raina's death.

465
00:22:45.760 --> 00:22:46.880
It's your fault.

466
00:22:47.880 --> 00:22:49.000
It's Dre.

467
00:22:53.760 --> 00:22:55.840
But what if your plan goes wrong. Ghost?

468
00:22:57.320 --> 00:22:59.240
[both laugh]

469
00:23:02.520 --> 00:23:05.080
-Tonight. oh. my God.
-[both moan]

470
00:23:05.200 --> 00:23:06.880
All right. all right.

471
00:23:07.960 --> 00:23:09.960
-Tommy. Tommy.
-Why stop?

472
00:23:11.200 --> 00:23:13.200
-Tonight meant so much to me.
-Yeah?

473
00:23:13.320 --> 00:23:14.360
Yes.

474
00:23:15.520 --> 00:23:16.760
They weren't too tough on you?

475
00:23:17.720 --> 00:23:19.160
You know. sometimes. old folks.

476
00:23:19.320 --> 00:23:20.800
they got a certain way
of looking at things.

477
00:23:21.120 --> 00:23:22.400
No. I can handle it.

478
00:23:22.960 --> 00:23:24.120
[laughs]

479
00:23:24.800 --> 00:23:27.440
And you stuck up for me.

480
00:23:29.000 --> 00:23:30.160
That's what matters.

481
00:23:32.280 --> 00:23:33.600
[knock on door]

482
00:23:34.560 --> 00:23:35.840
What the fuck?

483
00:23:38.680 --> 00:23:40.240
Who you got coming over
this late at night?

484
00:23:40.920 --> 00:23:42.600
Tommy. ain't no nigga
coming over here.

485
00:23:43.080 --> 00:23:44.280
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

486
00:23:44.920 --> 00:23:46.760
-Let me answer the door.
-Go ahead.

487
00:23:47.360 --> 00:23:48.720
Answer the door.

488
00:23:53.920 --> 00:23:54.920
Fuck you want?

489
00:23:55.320 --> 00:23:57.320
-Is LaKeisha Grant here?
-Who wants to know?

490
00:23:57.800 --> 00:24:00.120
Yes. I'm here.

491
00:24:00.800 --> 00:24:03.040
-You've been served.
-Wait. come here.

492
00:24:03.920 --> 00:24:05.320
Better run. motherfucker.

493
00:24:13.600 --> 00:24:14.880
-What the fuck?
-What is it?

494
00:24:16.160 --> 00:24:19.000
A subpoena to appear
in front of a grand jury?

495
00:24:20.480 --> 00:24:21.400
For what?

496
00:24:22.200 --> 00:24:25.080
For the murder of Raymond Jones. NYPD.

497
00:24:27.320 --> 00:24:30.080
Tommy. is this about Tasha's alibi?

498
00:24:30.760 --> 00:24:32.640
The one she wanted me to give
for her and Tariq?

499
00:24:34.920 --> 00:24:37.160
-Yo. you said it wouldn't come to this.
-I know.

500
00:24:39.720 --> 00:24:41.560
And when I said that.
I thought it wouldn't.

501
00:24:41.960 --> 00:24:43.320
So what am I supposed to do?

502
00:24:45.320 --> 00:24:46.920
Lying to the police is one thing.

503
00:24:47.240 --> 00:24:49.720
But lying in a courtroom. under oath?

504
00:24:50.320 --> 00:24:51.920
Yo. they could send you to jail for that.

505
00:24:53.360 --> 00:24:54.720
You gave Tasha your word.

506
00:24:56.880 --> 00:24:58.160
So that's what this is about.

507
00:25:00.680 --> 00:25:02.160
You coming back into my life.

508
00:25:04.080 --> 00:25:06.400
No. No way.

509
00:25:07.240 --> 00:25:08.600
You know better than that.

510
00:25:09.480 --> 00:25:12.200
I just don't want something bad happening
to the family because you got scared.

511
00:25:12.320 --> 00:25:13.520
I am scared.

512
00:25:14.360 --> 00:25:17.320
-And I got a goddamn right to be.
-I know. and it's fucked up.

513
00:25:18.480 --> 00:25:21.240
But I'll tell you this.
Tasha is smart. talk to her.

514
00:25:21.560 --> 00:25:24.480
If we gonna get out of this thing.
you got to do what she says.

515
00:25:26.760 --> 00:25:30.240
And then. we ain't fucking
with her or Ghost anymore.

516
00:25:31.680 --> 00:25:33.400
[exhales]

517
00:25:40.120 --> 00:25:41.600
[knock on door]

518
00:25:46.640 --> 00:25:48.160
[James] Hey. son.
I got a question for you.

519
00:25:48.480 --> 00:25:51.960
When you were running with Kanan.
you ever see Dre and Ray Ray together?

520
00:25:53.040 --> 00:25:56.000
Yep. in your friend. Breeze's apartment.
where you killed him.

521
00:25:57.440 --> 00:25:58.440
Did Kanan tell you that?

522
00:26:01.680 --> 00:26:03.080
You killed your own friend. Breeze.

523
00:26:04.080 --> 00:26:06.800
For some territory?
To get ahead in the game?

524
00:26:07.400 --> 00:26:08.520
Breeze was a bad dude.

525
00:26:09.240 --> 00:26:10.560
He was gonna get us all killed.

526
00:26:11.520 --> 00:26:13.560
You come in here
asking me about Kanan. why?

527
00:26:14.160 --> 00:26:15.520
You want to frame him again?

528
00:26:16.200 --> 00:26:18.040
Tariq. I do what I need to do
to solve problems.

529
00:26:19.040 --> 00:26:21.960
I'm not framing Kanan to solve this one.
I promise you that.

530
00:26:23.240 --> 00:26:25.840
You're going to frame Dre. How though?

531
00:26:26.160 --> 00:26:27.640
He wasn't there. how are you
going to prove he was there?

532
00:26:28.400 --> 00:26:29.520
And then what if that doesn't work?

533
00:26:30.160 --> 00:26:31.960
-Then Mom goes to jail?
-No. if that doesn't work.

534
00:26:32.120 --> 00:26:33.280
then I turn myself in for Ray Ray.

535
00:26:33.480 --> 00:26:35.520
Not your mother. I'm your father.
your life is my responsibility.

536
00:26:36.200 --> 00:26:38.240
Yeah. right.
you'll just find another way out.

537
00:26:44.640 --> 00:26:46.000
You're my son. all right?

538
00:26:46.640 --> 00:26:48.520
And what that means is
I would do anything for you.

539
00:26:49.160 --> 00:26:50.160
Including sacrificing my life

540
00:26:50.280 --> 00:26:51.920
to give you the future
I think you deserve.

541
00:26:52.640 --> 00:26:55.160
You don't have to believe it.
but it's true.

542
00:26:57.000 --> 00:26:59.040
So you're going to jail. not Ma?

543
00:26:59.800 --> 00:27:02.120
Tariq. no one in this family is going
to jail if I can help it.

544
00:27:02.280 --> 00:27:05.320
but yes. I'll take the rap. not Ma.

545
00:27:19.400 --> 00:27:20.320
Tariq.

546
00:27:21.120 --> 00:27:22.360
We need to talk.

547
00:27:23.200 --> 00:27:27.280
-Twenty. 40. 60. 80. 100.
-Yeah. yeah. I know how much it was.

548
00:27:27.400 --> 00:27:30.440
-How the fuck did you make that shot?
-[laughs]

549
00:27:30.760 --> 00:27:32.440
Yo. your game is on today.

550
00:27:33.040 --> 00:27:34.160
I've been thinking about this shit.

551
00:27:34.640 --> 00:27:38.120
How did you and Ghost get close enough
to Diego Jimenez to pull that trigger?

552
00:27:39.000 --> 00:27:41.360
From what I can come up with.
Dre wanted Diego dead.

553
00:27:42.040 --> 00:27:42.960
Ghost made a deal.

554
00:27:43.680 --> 00:27:44.800
With Dre?

555
00:27:45.080 --> 00:27:47.640
-Why the fuck would he do that?
-Why is not the question.

556
00:27:47.920 --> 00:27:50.280
What you should be asking yourself is.
what's Dre's side of the deal?

557
00:27:51.320 --> 00:27:54.000
Who's supposed to get dead? Me. you?

558
00:27:54.360 --> 00:27:55.440
[door opens]

559
00:27:55.880 --> 00:27:57.160
[alarm chirps]

560
00:27:57.520 --> 00:27:59.280
-What up. fellas?
-What's up. Ghost?

561
00:27:59.680 --> 00:28:01.040
Hey. Tommy. I need to rap
with you for a minute.

562
00:28:01.200 --> 00:28:02.360
K. you mind if we have the room?

563
00:28:02.520 --> 00:28:04.720
You always send a motherfucker
out the room like a goddamn kid.

564
00:28:05.480 --> 00:28:07.160
Like you forget who taught you
the game in the first place.

565
00:28:07.600 --> 00:28:08.840
Yo. K. you ain't got to go.

566
00:28:09.720 --> 00:28:10.920
I was headed out. anyway.

567
00:28:13.960 --> 00:28:14.960
Y'all play nice.

568
00:28:18.240 --> 00:28:19.320
Later. K.

569
00:28:20.440 --> 00:28:22.560
Did you know that LaKeisha
got a subpoena

570
00:28:22.680 --> 00:28:24.120
to appear in front of a grand jury?

571
00:28:24.720 --> 00:28:26.960
-Shit.
-You goddamn right. shit.

572
00:28:27.520 --> 00:28:29.360
She got to go under oath. and lie about

573
00:28:29.480 --> 00:28:32.200
where 'Riq and Tasha were
the night Ray Ray got shot.

574
00:28:32.720 --> 00:28:33.880
I think I got a plan. Tommy.

575
00:28:34.320 --> 00:28:35.760
It'll keep 'Keisha and all of us safe.

576
00:28:35.920 --> 00:28:38.040
-Yeah. why don't that make me feel better?
-Look. when I was on the inside.

577
00:28:38.160 --> 00:28:39.680
was Dre running product through Truth?

578
00:28:40.080 --> 00:28:41.240
Because I did the books. Tommy.

579
00:28:41.640 --> 00:28:42.680
He made too much money in there.

580
00:28:43.760 --> 00:28:45.560
-Yeah. that's how we did it.
-We?

581
00:28:46.040 --> 00:28:47.440
And you got an issue
with me keeping secrets?

582
00:28:47.560 --> 00:28:50.080
Come on. Tommy. do you understand
how much you put at risk by doing that?

583
00:28:50.240 --> 00:28:51.520
Yeah. I do. my life.

584
00:28:52.160 --> 00:28:54.600
Milan kept us in it.
Petar said keep going.

585
00:28:54.800 --> 00:28:55.840
-I didn't have a choice.
-Okay. Tommy.

586
00:28:55.960 --> 00:28:57.640
I'll just use that. all right?

587
00:28:57.880 --> 00:29:00.200
I'll say I fired Dre for running drugs
through the club.

588
00:29:00.560 --> 00:29:02.960
Then he reached out to his contact.
Ray Ray. to get revenge on me.

589
00:29:03.800 --> 00:29:04.880
Of course. we've got to make sure

590
00:29:05.000 --> 00:29:06.520
that we keep his drug dealing
separate from ours.

591
00:29:06.640 --> 00:29:08.920
And then when we kill that nigga.
we just drop a La Arana card on him.

592
00:29:09.280 --> 00:29:10.360
Yo. I got one better.

593
00:29:11.280 --> 00:29:12.840
We still got Diego's head. right?

594
00:29:13.400 --> 00:29:15.320
We drop that shit in Dre's place.

595
00:29:16.040 --> 00:29:17.280
that gives the Jimenez motive.

596
00:29:18.440 --> 00:29:20.640
That's better. and then we drop
the murder weapon on him. too.

597
00:29:20.960 --> 00:29:23.480
Wait. what the fuck murder weapon?
Tasha said she got rid of the gun.

598
00:29:24.000 --> 00:29:25.120
She told me the same shit.

599
00:29:25.680 --> 00:29:27.040
I'll explain later. all right?

600
00:29:29.000 --> 00:29:30.560
I ain't usually ride dirty like this.

601
00:29:30.920 --> 00:29:33.000
not since I got caught
thanks to your mom and pop.

602
00:29:33.640 --> 00:29:35.200
I'm a little short on manpower these days.

603
00:29:35.640 --> 00:29:36.560
Pfft. don't worry about it.

604
00:29:36.680 --> 00:29:39.600
-Ghost gonna get his time sooner or later.
-You going to fuck Ghost up?

605
00:29:39.920 --> 00:29:42.080
No. Ghost going to fuck himself up.

606
00:29:42.800 --> 00:29:44.560
He thinking about taking the rap for me

607
00:29:44.720 --> 00:29:46.480
-on this whole Ray Ray shit.
-[laughs]

608
00:29:46.760 --> 00:29:49.120
I ain't never know Ghost
to roll over like no little bitch.

609
00:29:49.560 --> 00:29:50.960
Motherfucker win. no matter what.

610
00:29:51.760 --> 00:29:53.120
You don't believe that shit though. right?

611
00:29:53.640 --> 00:29:56.200
I mean. I don't know.
He seemed real enough about it.

612
00:29:57.120 --> 00:29:59.320
I think he might try to pin all of it
on Dre first.

613
00:29:59.760 --> 00:30:03.080
Now. that do sound like Ghost.
Maybe you can trust that nigga.

614
00:30:03.520 --> 00:30:04.440
Close the trunk.

615
00:30:04.800 --> 00:30:07.560
Let's take this shit to the "Eye-talians".
and then I want to show you something.

616
00:30:28.360 --> 00:30:30.360
Don't you already have everything
you wanted?

617
00:30:31.200 --> 00:30:32.840
Relax. I'm gonna do you a favor.

618
00:30:32.960 --> 00:30:34.680
Oh. you're gonna do me a favor. really?

619
00:30:35.120 --> 00:30:36.200
After blackmailing me?

620
00:30:37.000 --> 00:30:38.400
That just means we're on the same side.

621
00:30:39.160 --> 00:30:41.920
My advice is that you distance yourself
from Andre.

622
00:30:42.800 --> 00:30:45.320
If you don't. you won't win the election.

623
00:30:46.000 --> 00:30:49.160
I'm going to need more than your word.
and your spite.

624
00:30:55.960 --> 00:30:57.000
Here's the truth.

625
00:30:57.920 --> 00:30:59.320
I fired Andre.

626
00:31:00.040 --> 00:31:01.760
Because while I was wrongfully imprisoned.

627
00:31:02.400 --> 00:31:04.880
I suspected he was pushing drugs
through this club.

628
00:31:05.400 --> 00:31:08.120
I was right. and ever since.
your friend. Andre.

629
00:31:08.480 --> 00:31:09.880
has had a vendetta against me.

630
00:31:10.800 --> 00:31:12.360
Why are you telling me this shit now?

631
00:31:12.640 --> 00:31:15.280
Because he's pulling the same tricks
with the Basset hotel group.

632
00:31:15.400 --> 00:31:16.720
I can tell because of how much money

633
00:31:16.880 --> 00:31:18.480
they've made in such a short amount
of time.

634
00:31:19.240 --> 00:31:20.280
He's in with some bad people.

635
00:31:21.080 --> 00:31:22.840
and it's going to come down
on him real soon.

636
00:31:23.240 --> 00:31:25.120
which means that if you don't break ties
with him.

637
00:31:25.520 --> 00:31:27.000
he's gonna drag you to the bottom.

638
00:31:28.960 --> 00:31:30.240
What about you. James?

639
00:31:32.000 --> 00:31:33.320
You stick close to me.

640
00:31:34.240 --> 00:31:36.200
And I'll be pulling you up
with me to the top.

641
00:31:41.800 --> 00:31:44.320
Back in the days. me. Tommy.
and your pops used to run this block.

642
00:31:45.000 --> 00:31:47.040
We was around your age.
we was selling crack

643
00:31:47.160 --> 00:31:48.680
a hundred miles an hour up the street.

644
00:31:49.440 --> 00:31:51.040
Until the cops started to know our faces.

645
00:31:52.000 --> 00:31:53.760
Every time they seen us.
they used to hop out.

646
00:31:54.040 --> 00:31:55.000
run down on us.

647
00:31:55.880 --> 00:31:58.120
Ghost would be gone before we could
even think to run and shit.

648
00:32:00.240 --> 00:32:02.360
See. he-- He ain't try to outrun the cops.

649
00:32:03.160 --> 00:32:06.240
He just figured that as long as
he could outrun me and Tommy.

650
00:32:06.440 --> 00:32:07.360
the cops would settle for us.

651
00:32:07.840 --> 00:32:10.200
[scoffs]
Nigga always thinking about himself.

652
00:32:12.040 --> 00:32:13.360
Well. it's worked for him so far.

653
00:32:17.400 --> 00:32:19.760
Take these dimes.
hit me when you get them off.

654
00:32:20.320 --> 00:32:21.400
When I get them off?

655
00:32:22.000 --> 00:32:23.400
How the fuck I'm supposed to do that?

656
00:32:23.920 --> 00:32:25.440
-I don't know these people.
-Figure it out.

657
00:32:25.800 --> 00:32:27.200
Don't come back until you do.

658
00:32:27.920 --> 00:32:29.040
Just don't get caught.

659
00:32:29.440 --> 00:32:30.400
All right.

660
00:32:37.400 --> 00:32:39.880
-Hey.
-Congratulations.

661
00:32:40.240 --> 00:32:43.480
-Got your law license back.
-Ha. appreciate it.

662
00:32:45.640 --> 00:32:48.840
So hey. uh. yeah.
I was going through old files.

663
00:32:49.000 --> 00:32:50.520
trying to get back up to speed. and...

664
00:32:51.200 --> 00:32:54.640
you know that guard at the MCC
who was giving you a hard time?

665
00:32:56.760 --> 00:32:58.960
Well. he was brutally murdered.

666
00:33:01.680 --> 00:33:04.200
You don't know anything about that. right?

667
00:33:05.840 --> 00:33:08.520
-[grunts]
-Good. that's good.

668
00:33:08.880 --> 00:33:13.040
In-- In not knowing anything about that.
because I wasn't your counsel at the time.

669
00:33:16.320 --> 00:33:19.240
There wouldn't have been
any witnesses. would there?

670
00:33:23.440 --> 00:33:25.120
So there's potential exposure?

671
00:33:27.480 --> 00:33:29.040
Could be. Did something happen. Joe?

672
00:33:29.640 --> 00:33:32.400
No. no. I am just doing my job.

673
00:33:32.920 --> 00:33:35.360
-which is watching your back.
-Well. I appreciate that.

674
00:33:36.360 --> 00:33:37.720
But I do have a question for you.

675
00:33:40.800 --> 00:33:44.680
Let's say I decide to take the rap
for something I didn't do.

676
00:33:45.040 --> 00:33:46.680
What's the collateral damage?

677
00:33:48.120 --> 00:33:50.840
-Care to be more specific?
-I can't be.

678
00:33:54.440 --> 00:33:57.440
Hypothetically. if you turn yourself
in for something.

679
00:33:57.800 --> 00:34:00.160
there is no way the state
is not gonna use that

680
00:34:00.280 --> 00:34:02.440
as an excuse to dig deeper
into your life.

681
00:34:02.880 --> 00:34:05.440
And you already got a big target
on your back. buddy.

682
00:34:07.560 --> 00:34:10.160
And what about the others
who are close to me?

683
00:34:11.600 --> 00:34:14.600
Is this what you were talking
about with Angela and Tasha?

684
00:34:15.400 --> 00:34:16.680
You know what. forget I asked about it.

685
00:34:16.840 --> 00:34:17.800
-No.
-Stupid idea.

686
00:34:17.920 --> 00:34:20.920
James. come on.
You can trust me. okay?

687
00:34:21.440 --> 00:34:22.480
I'm watching your back.

688
00:34:23.320 --> 00:34:24.680
The more you tell me.

689
00:34:25.000 --> 00:34:26.920
that's the better I can advise you.

690
00:34:28.600 --> 00:34:30.760
Now. come on. James. you-- Let me in.

691
00:34:34.480 --> 00:34:35.640
Thanks. Joe.

692
00:34:37.720 --> 00:34:38.800
Good seeing you.

693
00:34:39.440 --> 00:34:40.600
[exhales]

694
00:34:43.720 --> 00:34:46.000
And then. this guy knocked on
my door and handed this to me.

695
00:34:47.360 --> 00:34:50.200
I'm being asked to appear
on the witness stand in a grand jury.

696
00:34:52.520 --> 00:34:53.800
This is about you and Tariq. right?

697
00:34:54.680 --> 00:34:55.880
No. it's about Ghost.

698
00:34:56.640 --> 00:34:58.960
They think he murdered the man
who killed Raina.

699
00:34:59.120 --> 00:35:01.560
-Did he?
-No. he didn't.

700
00:35:02.000 --> 00:35:03.960
But the man who did is still out there.

701
00:35:04.320 --> 00:35:06.880
and the police aren't going after him.
They're coming after us.

702
00:35:07.400 --> 00:35:09.280
What's your man. Silver.
saying about all this?

703
00:35:09.600 --> 00:35:12.000
-How can he help?
-He can't.

704
00:35:14.720 --> 00:35:16.080
You know the alibi I asked you for?

705
00:35:16.400 --> 00:35:18.560
-For me. Ghost. Tariq--
-Tommy.

706
00:35:18.680 --> 00:35:19.600
Yes.

707
00:35:21.760 --> 00:35:22.920
Well. I need one more.

708
00:35:23.760 --> 00:35:25.880
It's for the person
who we think killed Ray Ray.

709
00:35:28.800 --> 00:35:29.760
Hold up. Tash.

710
00:35:31.000 --> 00:35:34.320
So you saying you know who killed
Raina's killer. right?

711
00:35:35.520 --> 00:35:37.400
But you're not going to go to the cops
and tell them that.

712
00:35:38.040 --> 00:35:39.680
You want me to get on the witness stand.

713
00:35:40.400 --> 00:35:43.320
and risk my freedom and my life.
to lie for you instead?

714
00:35:43.440 --> 00:35:46.000
'Keisha. I got you.
You know I would never let that happen.

715
00:35:46.400 --> 00:35:47.480
How is it that you got me?

716
00:35:48.040 --> 00:35:49.560
Have I ever asked you to commit perjury?

717
00:35:50.160 --> 00:35:52.680
Have I ever hijacked your business
to clean drug money?

718
00:35:53.400 --> 00:35:56.520
Even on a basic level. Tash.
Yas been over here a million times.

719
00:35:57.200 --> 00:35:58.880
When's the last time
you laid eyes on Cash?

720
00:36:02.400 --> 00:36:03.600
You know what. you're right.

721
00:36:06.320 --> 00:36:08.360
I admit it. I haven't been
a very good friend.

722
00:36:10.520 --> 00:36:13.400
But I have kept all of my promises.

723
00:36:16.600 --> 00:36:18.320
You know what. if you don't want
to do this for me.

724
00:36:18.520 --> 00:36:19.560
